  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0033.agda" type="external">erct-0033.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>A</tex> be a <link href="erct-0010.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0010" title="Path object">path object</link>. Any <link href="erct-0031.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0031" title="Cocartesian family of path objects">cocartesian family of path objects</link> <tex>B \colon  A \to   \mathsf {PathObj}</tex> gives rise to a canonical <link href="erct-0012.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0012" title="Displayed path object">displayed path object</link> over <tex>A</tex> in which:</p><ol><li>for <tex>p \colon  x \cong _A y</tex>, we define <tex>b \cong _B^p b'</tex> to be <tex>p_*b  \cong _{By} b'</tex>;</li>
 <li>for <tex>x:A</tex> and <tex>b:Bx</tex>, the identity element <tex>1_{ b } \colon  b \cong _B^{ 1_{ x } }b</tex> is given by the component <tex>\Phi _Bxb \colon   \mathopen {} \left ( 1_{ x } \right ) \mathclose {} _*b \cong _{Bx}b</tex> of the unit law of <tex>B</tex>.</li></ol>
 
   
   
 
</mainmatter> </tree></context> <related/> <backlinks/> <references/></backmatter></tree>